ool calls: 22","-- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 7, Edit: 13, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~800 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)","-- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads","-- Redundant operations: one file read twice (workflow-parser.test.ts)","-","-### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — code-review (2026-04-03T02:55)","-","-- **HIGH fixed:** ~75 lines duplicated validation/integrity/defaults between `parseWorkflow()` and `resolveWorkflow()`. Extracted `validateAndResolve()`.","-- **HIGH fixed:** `loadWorkflowPatch` silently swallowed EACCES permission errors. Now throws on permission errors, null only for missing files.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** Empty catch clause in embedded workflow loading discarded original error message.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** No test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'custom' })` path. Added.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** `deepMerge` duplicated in agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** Custom workflow detection re-reads file that `parseWorkflow` also reads (minor I/O waste).","-- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.","-","-## Token Report — code-review","-- Total tool calls: 18","-- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines)","-- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads","-- Redundant operations: none","-","-### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — verification (2026-04-03T02:58)","-","-- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC N:` (h3) instead of `## AC N:` (h2) and lacked bash/output block pairs. Rewrote.","-- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking.","-- **BATS integration tests:** All show exit code 127 (pre-existing, unrelated).","-- **Branch coverage 79.12%:** Below 80% for branches specifically, but AC says \"80%+ coverage\" without specifying branches. Statement 93.96%, functions 100%.","-- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.","-","-## Token Report — verification","-- Total tool calls: 16","-- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test | tail -80` (~80 lines), `vitest run workflow-parser.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (~45 lines)","-- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads","-- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice, npm run test:unit run twice","-","-### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — create-story (2026-04-03T07:06)","-","-- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic's ACs for story 9.2 are sparse (3 lines). Expanded to 10 ACs covering error paths, backward compatibility, edge cases (custom + patch coexistence), and agent resolution.","-- **Story is smaller than expected:** Most heavy lifting done in story 9-1. resolveWorkflow() already accepts a `name` parameter and detects full custom workflows. This story is primarily CLI plumbing + test coverage.","-- **Risk — user-level custom workflows unsupported:** resolveWorkflow() only checks project-level for full custom workflows. User-level custom workflows are only supported as patches, not full workflows.","-","-## Token Report — create-story","-- Total tool calls: 17","-- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 6, Edit: 0, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 5","-- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads","-- Redundant operations: Two separate Glob calls for same pattern — minor","-","-### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — dev-story (2026-04-03T07:10)","-","-No issues reported. Clean implementation — existing resolveWorkflow() already supported the name parameter.","-","-## Token Report — dev-story","-- Total tool calls: 12","-- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Glob: 2","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)","-- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads","-- Redundant operations: none","-","-### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — code-review (2026-04-03T07:15)","-","-- **HIGH fixed:** Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (`err` → `fallbackErr`).","-- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test assertions strengthened for `cwd` and error message content.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicate test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` between 9.2 section and pre-existing test.","-- **LOW (not fixed):** Legacy fallback path in run.ts should eventually be removed.","-- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.","-","-## Token Report — code-review","-- Total tool calls: 19","-- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff` (~200 lines)","-- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads","-- Redundant operations: none","-","-### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — verification (2026-04-03T07:20)","-","-- **Proof format issues:** Initial proof had 8/10 ACs because ACs 9-10 lacked bash+output paired code blocks. Fixed.","-- **Tier header mismatch:** Proof used `**Verification tier:**` instead of `**Tier:**` — validator regex only matches latter. Fixed.","-- **Observation:** Vitest ANSI escape codes make grep-based extraction unreliable from raw output.","-","-## Token Report — verification","-- Total tool calls: 20","-- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 4, Grep: 8, Edit: 3, Write: 1","-- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines ANSI), `npm run test:unit -- --coverage` (~100 lines)","-- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads","-- Redundant operations: Coverage and test:unit run separately (could be one), verify run 3 times due to proof format fixes","-","-### 10-2-driver-factory-registry — verification (2026-04-03T10:55)","-","-- `codeharness verify` exits code 1 due to AGENTS.md doc-gate (missing factory.ts) — harness precondition, not AC failure","-- BATS integration tests show code 127 warnings — pre-