{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019XhNepX61x8dqhqsqeJi56","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 12.2: OpenCode Driver Implementation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to run tasks on OpenCode by setting `driver: opencode` in my workflow YAML,\n11\tso that I can use OpenCode's multi-model support for any task alongside other frameworks.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` file\n16\t   **When** inspected\n17\t   **Then** `OpenCodeDriver` implements the `AgentDriver` interface with `name = 'opencode'`, `defaultModel = 'default'` (inherits from OpenCode's own config), and `capabilities` including `supportsPlugins: true`, `supportsStreaming: true`, `costReporting: true`\n18\t   **And** the class structure matches `CodexDriver` (one file per driver, named export, stateless between dispatches except `lastCost`)\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** `OpenCodeDriver.dispatch(opts)` is called with a valid prompt\n22\t   **When** the driver executes\n23\t   **Then** it spawns `opencode` CLI via `child_process.spawn` with `stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']`\n24\t   **And** stdout is parsed line-by-line into `StreamEvent` objects\n25\t   **And** unparseable lines are logged at debug level and skipped (never thrown, never yielded as malformed events)\n26\t   **And** a `result` event is always yielded at the end, even on error\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t3. **Given** the OpenCode CLI reports cost in its output\n30\t   **When** `dispatch()` completes\n31\t   **Then** `cost_usd` is captured from CLI output and set on the final `result` event\n32\t   **And** `getLastCost()` returns the same value\n33\t   **And** if the CLI does not report cost, `cost_usd` is set to `null` (not 0, not undefined)\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t4. **Given** the OpenCode CLI exits with a non-zero exit code or outputs an error\n37\t   **When** the error is classified\n38\t   **Then** the driver maps it to one of the standard `ErrorCategory` values: `RATE_LIMIT`, `NETWORK`, `AUTH`, `TIMEOUT`, `UNKNOWN`\n39\t   **And** classification follows the documented priority order (429/rate limit -> RATE_LIMIT, network codes -> NETWORK, 401/403/unauthorized -> AUTH, timeout -> TIMEOUT, else -> UNKNOWN)\n40\t   **And** no new error categories are invented\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t5. **Given** `OpenCodeDriver.healthCheck()` is called\n44\t   **When** the `opencode` binary is installed on PATH\n45\t   **Then** it returns `{ available: true, authenticated: <auth_status>, version: <version_string> }`\n46\t   **And** when the binary is NOT on PATH, it returns `{ available: false, authenticated: false, version: null, error: \"opencode not found. Install: https://opencode.ai\" }`\n47\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n48\t\n49\t6. **Given** `dispatch()` receives `opts.timeout` with a value\n50\t   **When** the OpenCode CLI process runs longer than the timeout\n51\t   **Then** the process is killed\n52\t   **And** a `result` event with `errorCategory: 'TIMEOUT'` is yielded\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t7. **Given** `dispatch()` receives `opts.plugins` with values\n56\t   **When** the driver processes the plugins array\n57\t   **Then** it passes each plugin via `--plugin` flag to the OpenCode CLI\n58\t   **And** dispatch proceeds with plugins included in the CLI args\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t8. **Given** `dispatch()` produces `StreamEvent` objects\n62\t   **When** the sequence is inspected\n63\t   **Then** events follow the required ordering: zero or more `tool-start` -> `tool-input` -> `tool-complete` sequences, zero or more `text` events interleaved, zero or more `retry` events, and exactly one `result` event at the end\n64\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n65\t\n66\t9. **Given** `OpenCodeDriver` is exported from `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts`\n67\t   **When** `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` is inspected\n68\t   **Then** it re-exports `OpenCodeDriver` alongside existing exports\n69\t   **And** `factory.ts` provides the registration mechanism (the engine calls `registerDriver(new OpenCodeDriver())` at startup)\n70\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n71\t\n72\t10. **Given** fixture files in `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/`\n73\t    **When** unit tests run\n74\t    **Then** tests cover: successful dispatch with event ordering, error classification for each category, health check with binary found, health check with binary missing, timeout termination, plugins pass-through, cost capture, cost null when absent, unparseable line handling\n75\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n76\t\n77\t11. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n78\t    **When** the build completes\n79\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n80\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n81\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n82\t\n83\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n84\t\n85\t- [ ] Task 1: Create OpenCode CLI output fixtures (AC: #10)\n86\t  - [ ] Create `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/` directory\n87\t  - [ ] Add `success.txt` — sample successful OpenCode CLI output (text-based or NDJSON lines representing tool use, text output, and result with cost)\n88\t  - [ ] Add `error-rate-limit.txt` — sample output when rate-limited\n89\t  - [ ] Add `error-auth.txt` — sample output when authentication fails\n90\t  - [ ] Add `error-network.txt` — sample output for network failures\n91\t  - [ ] Add `unparseable.txt` — sample output with lines that don't match any known format\n92\t  - [ ] NOTE: OpenCode CLI output format is not publicly documented. Create plausible fixtures based on typical CLI agent output patterns. Actual format will need refinement against real CLI output. OpenCode is Go-based — output may differ from Node.js CLIs.\n93\t\n94\t- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #8)\n95\t  - [ ] Implement `OpenCodeDriver` class implementing `AgentDriver` interface\n96\t  - [ ] Set `name = 'opencode'`, `defaultModel = 'default'`, `capabilities = { supportsPlugins: true, supportsStreaming: true, costReporting: true }`\n97\t  - [ ] Implement `parseLine(line: string): StreamEvent | null` — parse one stdout line into a StreamEvent or null\n98\t  - [ ] Implement `classifyError(err: unknown): ErrorCategory` — reuse the same classification priority order from `codex.ts` (identical logic)\n99\t  - [ ] Implement `dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncGenerator<StreamEvent>` using `child_process.spawn('opencode', [...args], { stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'] })`\n100\t  - [ ] Build CLI args from `opts`: `--model`, `--cwd`, `--plugin` (per plugin in opts.plugins), prompt as positional or via stdin\n101\t  - [ ] Parse stdout line-by-line via `readline.createInterface`\n102\t  - [ ] Log unparseable lines at debug level, skip them\n103\t  - [ ] Handle process `close` event for crash detection\n104\t  - [ ] Implement timeout via `setTimeout` + `proc.kill()`\n105\t  - [ ] Pass `opts.plugins` as `--plugin <name>` flags (unlike Codex which warns and ignores)\n106\t  - [ ] Guarantee `result` event is always yielded (even on error)\n107\t  - [ ] Implement `healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth>` — (1) `which opencode`, (2) `opencode --version`, (3) optional auth check\n108\t  - [ ] Implement `getLastCost(): number | null`\n109\t\n110\t- [ ] Task 3: Update barrel export in `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` (AC: #9)\n111\t  - [ ] Add `export { OpenCodeDriver } from './opencode.js';`\n112\t\n113\t- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests `src/lib/agents/__tests__/opencode-driver.test.ts` (AC: #10, #11)\n114\t  - [ ] Mock `child_process.spawn` and `child_process.execFile` via `vi.mock`\n115\t  - [ ] Helper: `makeOpts(overrides)` for creating DispatchOpts\n116\t  - [ ] Helper: `collectEvents(iterable)` for gathering all events\n117\t  - [ ] Helper: `createMockProcess(stdoutLines, exitCode, stderrData)` — same pattern as `codex-driver.test.ts`\n118\t  - [ ] Test: successful dispatch produces correct StreamEvent sequence from fixture\n119\t  - [ ] Test: result event is always present at end\n120\t  - [ ] Test: cost captured from CLI output\n121\t  - [ ] Test: cost is null when CLI doesn't report it\n122\t  - [ ] Test: error classification for RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, AUTH, TIMEOUT, UNKNOWN\n123\t  - [ ] Test: healthCheck with binary found returns available: true\n124\t  - [ ] Test: healthCheck with binary not found returns available: false with install instructions\n125\t  - [ ] Test: timeout kills process and yields TIMEOUT result\n126\t  - [ ] Test: plugins array passed as `--plugin` flags to CLI\n127\t  - [ ] Test: unparseable lines logged and skipped\n128\t  - [ ] Anti-pattern: do NOT mock `child_process.spawn` directly. Feed fixture lines to the parser via `createMockProcess`.\n129\t\n130\t- [ ] Task 5: Verify build and tests (AC: #11)\n131\t  - [ ] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n132\t  - [ ] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n133\t\n134\t## Dev Notes\n135\t\n136\t### Architecture Compliance\n137\t\n138\tThis story implements Epic 3, Story 3.2 (mapped to sprint Epic 12, Story 12-2) \"OpenCode Driver Implementation\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers FR2 (detect CLI binary on PATH), FR3 (verify auth status), FR5 (spawn agent via driver CLI), FR7 (parse CLI output to StreamEvent), FR8 (capture/normalize cost), FR9 (classify errors into standard categories), FR10 (detect/report unparseable output).\n139\t\n140\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n141\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** `OpenCodeDriver` implements `AgentDriver` with `dispatch()` returning `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`. Same interface as `ClaudeCodeDriver` and `CodexDriver`.\n142\t- **Decision 2 (CLI-Wrapping Strategy):** `child_process.spawn` with `stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']`. No PTY. Line-by-line stdout parsing.\n143\t- **Decision 4 (Model Resolution):** `defaultModel = 'default'` — OpenCode inherits from its own config, unlike Codex which has `codex-mini`.\n144\t- **Decision 6 (Plugin Pass-Through):** OpenCode supports plugins via `--plugin` flag. Unlike Codex (warn and ignore), OpenCode passes plugins through.\n145\t- **Implementation Patterns:** One file per driver, named `opencode.ts`. Class name `OpenCodeDriver`. Named export. Register in factory — never auto-discover. Stateless between dispatches except `lastCost`.\n146\t\n147\t### Key Differences from CodexDriver (Story 12-1)\n148\t\n149\tThe OpenCode driver is structurally identical to CodexDriver with these differences:\n150\t\n151\t1. **Plugins supported:** OpenCode supports `--plugin <name>` flags. Codex warns and ignores. The `dispatch()` method must iterate `opts.plugins` and add `--plugin` args.\n152\t2. **Default model:** `'default'` instead of `'codex-mini'`. OpenCode inherits from its own config.\n153\t3. **Binary name:** `opencode` instead of `codex`.\n154\t4. **Install instructions:** `\"opencode not found. Install: https://opencode.ai\"` instead of npm install.\n155\t5. **Health check auth:** OpenCode auth check may use `opencode auth status` or similar. Same pattern as Codex — try the command, if it fails treat as unauthenticated.\n156\t6. **Output format:** OpenCode is Go-based. Output format may differ. The `parseLine()` function should handle the same NDJSON-style format as Codex initially, but may need refinement later against real output. If OpenCode uses a different JSON structure, adjust field names accordingly.\n157\t\n158\t### Current State of the Codebase\n159\t\n160\t- **`src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts`** — Reference implementation for CLI-wrapped drivers. 333 lines. Copy this structure, adjust for OpenCode differences.\n161\t- **`src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts`** — In-process driver using Agent SDK. Different pattern — do NOT copy this for OpenCode.\n162\t- **`src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`** — Module-singleton registry. `registerDriver()`, `getDriver()`, `listDrivers()`, `resetDrivers()`. OpenCodeDriver will be registered here by the engine at startup (story 12-3).\n163\t- **`src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts`** — Barrel file. Currently exports factory functions + `ClaudeCodeDriver` + `CodexDriver`. Must add `OpenCodeDriver`.\n164\t- **`src/lib/agents/types.ts`** — Defines `AgentDriver`, `DispatchOpts`, `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `ErrorCategory`. All types ready — no changes needed.\n165\t- **`src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`** — Defines `StreamEvent` union type. The OpenCode driver needs its own `parseLine()` for OpenCode output format.\n166\t- **`src/lib/agents/__tests__/codex-driver.test.ts`** — Reference test file for CLI-wrapped drivers. Follow this pattern exactly.\n167\t- **Test count as of last story:** 4404 tests pass across 165 test files (53 added by story 12-1).\n168\t\n169\t### What NOT to Do\n170\t\n171\t- Do NOT modify `factory.ts` — only import from it. Registration happens in the engine.\n172\t- Do NOT modify `types.ts` — all types are already defined.\n173\t- Do NOT modify `stream-parser.ts` — the OpenCode driver has its own line parsing logic.\n174\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` — engine registration of OpenCodeDriver is deferred to story 12-3.\n175\t- Do NOT modify `codex.ts` — it is the reference, not a shared base class.\n176\t- Do NOT mock `child_process.spawn` directly in tests — use `createMockProcess()` helper pattern from `codex-driver.test.ts`.\n177\t- Do NOT invent new error categories beyond RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK, AUTH, TIMEOUT, UNKNOWN.\n178\t- Do NOT use PTY allocation — use plain `child_process.spawn` with pipes.\n179\t- Do NOT auto-discover the driver — it must be explicitly registered.\n180\t- Do NOT share `classifyError()` between drivers via import — each driver has its own copy (architecture requires self-contained driver files).\n181\t\n182\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n183\t\n184\tFrom story 12-1 (Codex Driver Implementation):\n185\t- 53 new tests added, 4404 total passing across 165 test files.\n186\t- `classifyError()` exported as standalone function — same pattern needed for OpenCode.\n187\t- `parseLine()` exported as standalone function — same pattern needed.\n188\t- `IGNORE:` comments required on catch blocks for linter compliance (project convention).\n189\t- `createMockProcess()` helper in test file creates mock stdout Readable, stderr EventEmitter, and proc EventEmitter. Emits lines via `stdout.push()` then `stdout.push(null)`, followed by `proc.emit('close', exitCode)` on next tick.\n190\t- Cost captured from `result` type events via `cost_usd` field on parsed JSON.\n191\t- `yieldedResult` boolean guarantees exactly one result event.\n192\t- `closePromise` captured BEFORE readline iteration to avoid race condition where `close` fires during iteration.\n193\t\n194\tFrom story 11-2 (Workflow Referential Integrity Validation):\n195\t- Referential integrity validates driver names at parse time. Once `OpenCodeDriver` is registered, `driver: opencode` will pass validation.\n196\t- Validation skips driver checks when registry is empty.\n197\t\n198\t### Git Intelligence\n199\t\n200\tRecent commits (all in current sprint):\n201\t- `6edd1df` — story 12-1: Codex Driver Implementation\n202\t- `44c0b70` — story 11-2: workflow referential integrity validation\n203\t- `a4bf7e6` — story 11-1: workflow schema extension\n204\t- `f128064` — story 10-5: workflow engine driver integration\n205\t- `3717741` — story 10-4: model resolution module\n206\t\n207\tAll recent work is in the driver/workflow area. Patterns are consistent and fresh.\n208\t\n209\t### Project Structure Notes\n210\t\n211\tFiles to CREATE:\n212\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` — OpenCodeDriver class\n213\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/opencode-driver.test.ts` — Unit tests\n214\t- `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/success.txt` — Success fixture\n215\t- `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/error-rate-limit.txt` — Rate limit error fixture\n216\t- `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/error-auth.txt` — Auth error fixture\n217\t- `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/error-network.txt` — Network error fixture\n218\t- `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/unparseable.txt` — Unparseable lines fixture\n219\t\n220\tFiles to MODIFY:\n221\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/index.ts` — Add `OpenCodeDriver` re-export\n222\t\n223\tFiles NOT to modify:\n224\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` — consume only\n225\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts` — reference only, do not import from\n226\t- `src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` — reference only\n227\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — all types exist\n228\t- `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` — OpenCode has its own parser\n229\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — engine registration is story 12-3\n230\t- `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` — schema already supports `driver` field\n231\t\n232\t### Testing Patterns\n233\t\n234\tFollow `codex-driver.test.ts` patterns exactly:\n235\t- `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` for spawn and execFile\n236\t- Helper: `makeOpts(overrides)` for creating DispatchOpts\n237\t- Helper: `collectEvents(iterable)` for gathering all events\n238\t- Helper: `createMockProcess(stdoutLines, exitCode, stderrData)` — creates mock Readable stdout, EventEmitter stderr, EventEmitter proc with kill mock\n239\t- Test event ordering: tool-start, tool-input, tool-complete, text, result\n240\t- Test error paths: each ErrorCategory triggered by specific fixture input\n241\t- Test health check: mock `execFile` for `which opencode` and `opencode --version`\n242\t- Test plugins: verify `--plugin` flags appear in spawn args (unlike Codex which warns)\n243\t- Anti-pattern: do NOT mock spawn directly. Feed fixture lines to the parser via createMockProcess.\n244\t- Add `// IGNORE:` comments on empty catch blocks per project convention.\n245\t\n246\t### References\n247\t\n248\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 3.2: OpenCode Driver Implementation]\n249\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n250\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 2: CLI-Wrapping Strategy]\n251\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 4: Model Resolution Cascade]\n252\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through]\n253\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns — Driver Implementation Pattern]\n254\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns — StreamEvent Production Pattern]\n255\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns — Error Classification Pattern]\n256\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns — Health Check Pattern]\n257\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns — Testing Pattern for Drivers]\n258\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts — reference CLI-wrapped driver implementation]\n259\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/__tests__/codex-driver.test.ts — reference test patterns]\n260\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-1-codex-driver-implementation.md — previous story context]\n261\t\n262\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n263\t## Verification Requirements\n264\t\n265\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/12-2-opencode-driver-implementation-proof.md)\n266\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n267\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n268\t\n269\t## Documentation Requirements\n270\t\n271\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n272\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/12-2-opencode-driver-implementation.md\n273\t\n274\t## Testing Requirements\n275\t\n276\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n277\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n278\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n279\t\n280\t## Dev Agent Record\n281\t\n282\t### Agent Model Used\n283\t\n284\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n285\t\n286\t### Debug Log References\n287\t\n288\t### Completion Notes List\n289\t\n290\t### File List\n291\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015Nd7r2sEMSMuBp6wLG2mSf","session_id":"65932dfc-6881-4906-8881-56eaa8ade510","uuid":"2dd8ab50-af61-4605-8351-24a5be592590","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:21:26.327Z"}
